Surendra,<div><br></div><div>There is no &quot;release&quot; of gcc-4.8 yet, and my experience (not Open MPI related) with recent snapshots has encountered many bugs still to be fixed before any release.  Even if you could build Open MPI with gcc-4.8, I would not (at this time) trust it with any &quot;production&quot; jobs.</div>
<div><br></div><div>Looking at the config.log you attached, it looks like your installation of gcc is unable to run the &quot;as&quot; assembler, which probably means you don&#39;t have Apple Xcode installed (which is the preferred source of the assembler and linker on Mac OSX).  So, I doubt that you can even build a &quot;Hello, World!&quot; C program with your gcc installation - have you tried?</div>
